<?php include $_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/inc/doc.inc.php";?><title>Ka of Isis: Yan-o-pah</title><meta name="robots" content="robots.txt"><meta name="description" content="Demonstrating the use of a pure CSS throbber. Vernal Fall photographed by Eadweard Muybridge in 1872. The image is courtesy the Google Art Project."><?php include $_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/inc/css.inc.php";?><style>#throbberBox{position:relative;max-width:960px;height:160px;margin-top:1.5em;border:1px solid #eef5df;background:#eef5df url("http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/88/Eadweard_Muybridge_-_Pi-Wi-Ack_%28Shower_of_Stars%29%2C_Vernal_Fall%2C_400_Feet%2C_Valley_of_Yosemite_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg") center no-repeat;}.throbber{position:absolute;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;left:0;width:43px;height:43px;margin:auto;border:3px dashed #475f14;border-radius:50%;-webkit-animation:spin 2s linear infinite;animation:spin 2s linear infinite;}@-ms-keyframes spin{from{-ms-transform:rotate(0deg);}to{-ms-transform:rotate(360deg);}}@-webkit-keyframes spin{from{-webkit-transform:rotate(0deg);}to{-webkit-transform:rotate(360deg);}}@keyframes spin{from{transform:rotate(0deg);}to{transform:rotate(360deg);}}</style><?php include $_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/inc/jquery.inc.php";?><script src="jquery.waitforimages.min.js"></script><script>$(document).ready(function(){<?php include $_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/inc/jsmenu.inc.php";?>
/*	START Throbber related  */
$("#throbberBox").waitForImages({
	waitForAll: true,
	finished: function(){
		$(".throbber").css({"display":"none"});
	}
});
/*	END Throbber related  */
});</script></head><body><?php include $_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/inc/ie.inc.php";?><header id="masthead"><h1><a href="/">Ka of Isis</a></h1></header><?php include $_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/inc/nav.inc.php";?><article><h2>Demo page for the article <i>CSS throbbers &#8211;&#160;Part&#160;2</i></h2>
<!-- START Throbber related -->
<div id="throbberBox">
	<div class="throbber"></div>
</div>
<!-- END Throbber related -->
<p class="fig">Fig. Demonstrating a simple CSS throbber. Note that only a small part of the image is shown in the placeholder. This has been done to achieve a comparable user experience across the many different screen sizes and browser window settings out there. If you want to see Yan-o-pah as it was photographed in 1872, head off to <a href="https://www.google.com/culturalinstitute/asset-viewer/pi-wi-ack-shower-of-stars-vernal-fall-400-feet-valley-of-yosemite/oAHzyuVVaiydHw?projectId=art-project">the Google Art Project</a>.</p><p>The <a href="https://github.com/alexanderdickson/waitForImages">waitForImage</a> JavaScript plug-in for jQuery is used to hide the throbber once the image has fully downloaded. The plug-in should work with images referenced with <code>src</code> in HTML <code>img</code> tags and with images called via the <code>background-image</code> property in CSS.</p><p>In this example (with <em>this</em> throbber) the default <code>slideUp()</code> method in the plug-in distorts the look of the CSS throbber, so a <code>function</code> is called to hide the throbber as suggested by <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/29678878/add-timeout-to-waitforimages">jvan27</a> at Stack Overflow. Dissect the page source to see the implementation.</p><p>If the page is reloaded/refreshed to repeat the demonstration, the browser cache should (possibly) be emptied first.</p><p>Return to <a href="index.php">the parent article</a> for a discussion.</p></article><?php include $_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/inc/foot.inc.php";?>